data.title: Bibliograph
data.meta_description: An open data platform that grows library visibility through a collaboration of thousands of libraries and their service providers. Our mission is to build new pathways to libraries on the Web. Together, we share structured data and connect people with the books they want to read.

Summary

Caleb, a 24-year-old coder at the worldb2ss largest Internet company, wins a competition to spend a week at a retreat belonging to the companyb2ss reclusive CEO, Nathan. But when Caleb arrives he finds that he will have to participate in a fascinating experiment with the worldb2ss first true artificial intelligence, housed in the body of a beautiful robot woman, Ava. Truths, emotions, and motives are blurred as the relationship between Caleb, Ava, and Nathan intensifies
